It is hard to find where a consonant ends since some characters 
can be both consonants and vowels. It is therefore easier to 
use a ZWJ 200D character after every consonant and a
ZWNJ before every consonant. i.e. 200C 200D
Some tones are unmarked so substitute 200b ZWSP at this stage.
They will be stripped out later during the vowel & tone reordering
